Last year, South Korea was rocked by corruption scandals involving illegal donations to politicians.
President Roh Moo-Hyun called for a thorough investigation into the illicit funds donated by a Samsung executive.
The National Intelligence Service was asked to look into the case.
Amidst the scandal, the country's Ambassador to the United States offered his resignation.
Allegations surfaced that he acted as an intermediary for Samsung in distributing slush funds to presidential candidates.
The spy agency apologized for illegal wiretapping, sparking public outrage.
President Roh accepted the ambassador's resignation amidst growing pressure.
